status_message:
Midnight EST in the US. Same time the blackout started, it now ends. 

Thanks for sticking around. <3

Okay, vagueabonds. 

Again, we're partaking in the 72 hour blackout with several other pages in solidarity with #zuxit but we're not going to temporarily unpublish the page. We're keeping it up so we can still accept subs and respond to messages and so on, however we won't post anything for 72 hours firm. 

Being apart of "Weird Facebook" is pretty much the only reason I and possibly SEVERAL OF YOU even have Facebook anymore. Even though this kind of thing may be pointless in the long run, we want to stand with providing awareness that arbitrary censorship is as callous as it is irresponsible.

We're still here, so hit us up. Just don't be alarmed by inactivity for the next 3 days. 

Love you guys.
Sent by a fan on Instagram.

status_message:
We don't like to do share for share or otherwise blatantly shill for other pages, but if any of you know anything about weird Facebook, you'd know select ambient memes was practically the authority on it. 

Getting cucked by the zucc is getting out of hand. 

That's why we're participating.

Help Select Ambient Memes return to their former glory. 

After the blackout, expect more shares from their page

We're taking part in something called #Zuxit, a Facebook meme page blackout. Zuxit isn't an isolated action; it's part of an ongoing movement protesting Facebook's handling of reports and seemingly arbitrary bans on users and pages, and regardless of effectiveness we are continuously organizing event after event in order to spread awareness as far as possible. Too many pages have been banned for no reason and awareness is the only thing we've got, so even if this is a waste of time we will continue the drive as part of the FB meme community.

We will not be unpublishing as many other pages are doing, this way we can still receive fan submissions and messages from you guys, but we will not be posting for 3 days(starting midnight EST). See you on the other side, my loves.

Just a few dos and don'ts regarding fan subs for y'all.

DO submit quality pictures you took or made.
DO submit quality pictures with absolutely zero context. We love that shit.
DO submit funny pictures of your pets if they are good enough.

DON'T submit STALE content from other Facebook pages or 9gag or reddit or wherever people find their trash. We want to keep it fresh, and it's annoying having to take time out of my day to tell someone I saw their meme back in '07 when I was skipping school listening to dubstep. 
DON'T take it personally if your submission isn't posted. As much as we'd like to please everyone by posting everything that's submitted, a solid 50-66% of it is trash. 
DON'T ask us to share stuff from your page, we will ignore your messages. 

There's some more things I could write but I really shouldn't have to. It's simple. Submit to the page what you would want people to submit if it was yours. Easy pz lemon squeezy.
